{"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","remoteSource":{"fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159"},"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"centerOffset","symbolKind":"property","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector","text":"CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the left.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to zero and its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"type":"text","text":" to half the height of the view."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNAnnotation","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","kind":"symbol","title":"centerOffset","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object that corresponds to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. When an annotation’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNAnnotationView","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","type":"topic","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}]}}}